23/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have detained five people in connection with a series of arson attacks on mosques in districts around Istanbul, media reported on Monday (December 22nd). Arsonists targeted a total of 19 mosques in an unprecedented wave of attacks this month, causing limited damage but no casualties. (Anadolu news agency, Zaman, Hurriyet, Milliyet, Sabah, Reuters - 22/12/08) 
